honeywell.printer.configuration.ez

Class PrinterOptions

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterData
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterState
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterOptions
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class PrinterOptions
extends PrinterState
    This class handles the data from an {PO?} query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    BSCR Device
    CCF Device
    DPrinter Description
    FText Fixture String
    ISPI Device
    MManufacturing Date
    NSerial Number
    PPart Number
    RCertification Flag Status
    SSDIO Device
    TPrinter Type
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • PrinterOptions

        public PrinterOptions(ConnectionBase connection)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        connection - connection to printer

      • getSCRDevice_IsPresent

        public boolean getSCRDevice_IsPresent()
        Indicates if getSCRDevice() parameter is present.

        This function is useful to determine if the given parameter is supported on the current printer. Because of differences in configuration, hardware or version certain parameter may not exist and the results returned by the parameter getSCRDevice() may not be valid.

        Returns:
        If the parameter is present and valid true, false otherwise.
        See Also:
